Internet-Draft                                               Distributed Social Identity
Intended status: Informational                               February 2026
Expires: August 2026


      Distributed Social Identity (DSI)  
      A Decentralized Profile Specification Using vCard and RSS  

      Abstract  

         This document specifies a decentralized social profile format based on vCard 4.0, extended with non-standard properties to support distributed social networks. The specification introduces a mandatory `SOURCE` property to define the canonical location of the vCard, `X-FEED` properties for associating RSS/Atom feeds with the profile, and additional extensible properties for platform-specific identifiers or endorsements. These extensions aim to enable interoperable, self-hosted identity documents that integrate seamlessly with decentralized ecosystems while supporting extensibility for future use cases.


Status of This Memo

   This document is not an Internet Standards Track specification.  It
   is published for informational purposes and may be used freely for
   software implementation, federation protocols, or identity systems.


